Shaggy, you and Scooby should look around for more clues.
Boy, this mansion sure is creepy! I hope my uncle's okay.

JOE ESPOSITO
BIT BY A MOSQUITO
CONTRACTED THE PLAGUE
AND NOW IS FINITO

HERE LIES THE BODY 
OF MR. HIN-HUSSLE-
HERE LIES THE BODY 
OF MR. HIN-HUSSLE-
PERLEY-MCFURLY-
TIN-WHISTLE-
O'MUSCLE-
O'JANSON-
SMITH-HANSON-
JONES-MURRAY-MCMAME,
WHO CHOKED ON HIS GUM
WHILE A' SAYING HIS NAME.
Zoinks,Scoob! Looks like something creepy has been through here!
Like WOW! This tree is actually a secret passage! No wonder that ghost gets around so easily. C'mon, Scoob!

WHILE HOEING A ROW
OLD PETE MADE A 
BLUNDER.
HE HOED ON HIS TOE
AND NOW LIES SIX FEET
UNDER.

This grave says:
I MAY BE DEAD,
BUT I'M ALSO CRANKY!
GET OFF OF MY GRAVE
OR I'LL GIVE YE A SPANKY!

This grave says:
DIDN'T WASH HIS HANDS.

HERE LIES BENJAMIN FRANKLIN...
YES, THE BENJAMIN FRANKLIN!

HERE LIES THE MAN
WHO WROTE THIS GAME'S
PLOT,
BUT DON'T SHEAD A TEAR
HE DESERVED WHAT HE GOT.

This grave says:
WHAT ARE YOU LOOKIN' AT?

PORTLY MS. COURTLY
WASN'T BURIED AT ALL,
HER  BODY WAS TOO BIG
AND HER CASKET TOO SMALL.
I've got a creepy feeling, man! Like, I b-b-et that ghost came out of this g-g-grave!
Wait a minute, Scoob. What kinda ghost leaves footprints?

R.I.P. 
CHRISTOPHER TATE
WHAT DID HE DIE OF?
SOMETHING HE ATE.
CHOKED ON A SANDWICH
A HORRIBLE FATE
LIVED TO THE AGE OF
ONE HUNDRED AND EIGHT.

CRUSHED BY A BOULDER,
OLD BARRY BICKER,
WOULD STILL BE ALIVE
IF HE ONLY RAN QUICKER!
Jinkies! You Found them! Here, take this magnifying glass to help you look for clues!
Ghost or no ghost, we've got to get to the bottom of this mystery!
dfghdfghdfgh
Shaggy? Scooby? Is that you? I've lost my glasses again! Help me find them!
Jinkies! You found them! Here, take this magnifying glass to help you look for clues!
Hey look, gang! I found this scary ghost costume, only it's way too big for the groundskeeper, so that clears our one suspect!
Shaggy, you and Scooby should look around for more clues.
Boy, this mansion sure is creepy! I hope my uncle's okay.
Like, what do you know? A whole box of Scooby Snacks! This sure is one delicious dead end!
I bet I'm a suspect, right?! You think I'm the ghost, don't you?!
Great! This suit you kids found clears my name! Here you go, kids, take take this extra mansion key. Please find Mr. Maxwell
Thanks again, kids. Please find Mr. Maxwell.

ON SEPTEMBER THE 10TH
THIS SWIMMER WAS KILLED
HE DOVE INTO THE POOL
BEFORE IT WAS FILLED.

SUZY O'BRIEN
WAS EATEN BY LIONS
WHEN SHE TOOK A TRIP TO THE ZOO.
WHAT WAS HER FAILING?
SHE LET GO OF THE RAILING.
LET THIS BE A LESSON FOR YOU.

R.I.P.
YOLANDA HINKS
BORN 1948
DIED 1924.
NO, WE DON'T KNOW HOW SHE DID IT, EITHER.
ZOINKS! It's that creepy ghost again! Let's get out of here!
ZOINKS! It's that creepy ghost again! Let's get out of here!
I know the ghost has Mr. Maxwell locked inside the mansion. If only I had a spare key!
You found a house key! Let's go through the gate and find Mr. Maxwell and that ghost!
Yikes! Creepy bats!
Yikes! Creepy Bats!
Like, WOW! We found Velma's glasses!
Zoinks! A G-G-GHOST! Let's scram, Scoob!
Like, what's with this old log? I'm stumped! Get it, Scoob? Stumped!
I see a trick door in this stump! Hey, there's a movie projector inside! Like, that scary ghost is just a filmstrip!
This is that trick stump where we found that projector!
No Way, Man! I'm not going one step further! I've had enough of that spooky graveyard to last me a lifetime!
Wow Scoob, you found a shortcut.
This shortcut's a lifesaver.
